    {
      "id": "node-1782630266913-0-cmy7",
      "label": "Memory Stress Testing Best Practices [chunk 1/4]",
      "type": "fact",
      "tier": "training",
      "content": "Memory Stress Testing Best Practices:\n\n1. CONCURRENT WRITES: Test with 50+ parallel writes to verify the debounced async write doesn't drop data. The graph should persist all writes within 200ms.\n\n2. CONCURRENT READS: Test with 50+ parallel searches to verify the sidecar's thread pool executor doesn't block. Search latency should stay under 50ms even under load.\n\n3. WRITE-THEN-READ: Write a node, then immediately search for it.",
      "tags": [
        "stress-test",
        "training",
        "best-practices",
        "training-material",
        "stress-test-training-guide"
      ],
      "entities": [
