    {
      "id": "node-1782630266913-1-tuzz",
      "label": "Memory Stress Testing Best Practices [chunk 2/4]",
      "type": "fact",
      "tier": "training",
      "content": "EAD: Write a node, then immediately search for it. The in-memory graph should return the new node instantly (no disk flush needed for reads).\n\n4. INDEX CONSISTENCY: After writes, verify the sidecar's index matches the graph's node count. The file watcher should detect the change and rebuild incrementally.\n\n5. TIER VALIDATION: Verify STM nodes get TTL, LTM nodes don't. Check auto-promotion after 3+ accesses. Check that training materials get confidence=0.95.\n\n6.",
